         <abstract>
            <p>According to a conjecture of Sato and Tate, the angle θ whose cosine is 1/2τ(p)p&lt;sup&gt;-11/2&lt;/sup&gt;, where τ is Ramanujan's function and p a prime, is distributed over [ 0, π ] according to a &lt;tex-math&gt;$\sin^2\theta$&lt;/tex-math&gt; law. The paper reports on a test of this conjecture for the 1229 primes under 10000. Extreme values of θ are also given.</p>
          </abstract>
